  "prompt": "How do you know who viewed you video on Instagram?",
  "response": "As of my last training data in October 2023, Instagram does not provide a feature that allows you to see exactly who viewed your videos. You can see the total number of views and any likes or comments that your video has received, but individual viewer information is not disclosed.\n\nIf you're curious about who might be engaging with your content, pay attention to who is liking and commenting on your videos. These interactions can give you a sense of your audience, even if you can't see exactly who viewed the video.\n\nTo focus on growing your engagement, consider interacting with your followers, posting consistent and quality content, and utilizing Instagram's various features like Stories, IGTV, and Reels to reach a wider audience.",
